# Curated denylist for tools/check-secrets.sh — the sensitive literals that
# are NOT `.env` values and so the .env-derived layer can't see (third-party
# names, product/brand names, anything confidential-but-not-a-config-value).
#
# Copy to `.claude/secret-strings` (gitignored) and fill with REAL values.
# One literal per line; `#` comments and blank lines ignored. Matched
# case-insensitively as whole words, so distinctive names are safe to list.
#
# Placeholders below are OBVIOUSLY FAKE — never put a real value in THIS file
# (it is committed). Real values go only in `.claude/secret-strings`.

Acme
ExampleCorp
SomeClientName
